column5: Nothing better than getting up into dimer, GB and GW....good to see that there are still some fish around.  Lots of snow still?  Good work buddy.
Gotta love the north!!!!!!  Now if I could just move our distribution center up there
nice fish  Great pics
Great pics and report Amazing brookies!

Still lots of snow last weekend although I think they got pummeled by rain this week.  We didn't actually make it to GW but we got those bigger fish from Moulder... and here I thought it was just a swamp! Heading back to try something easier this weekend!  Luc
Good luck this weekend.  Apr 20-25, shirk all responsibilities...its going to be steelhead madness.  Prepare yourself. The soundtrack

After all the housework this fall/winter I'm pretty sure I'll be well into "shirking" by then, and it will likely continue until the brookies stop biting in june.  Snowpacks this year should help fill the reservoirs that were so empty last year...

Saturday I headed north with two friends for some backcountry brookies.  We made a 2 hour hike into a chain of lakes we were familiar with and weren't disappointed.  We caught somewhere over 30 fish for the day including some real fat fish from the one lake.  Each of us kept a limit of small/badly hooked fish and we released just as many.  Not a lot of pics to share but of the unfortunate souls that became dinner.  Back up north for some spring fishing this weekend!  There's also a few other pics taken from various snowmobile trips/drunken weekends at camp...  Dr. Sal  Some nice brookies   A slow but steady February produced a lot of days like this at camp   I finally got my wife and son on the sled... note the potty on my lap!   One day we drove into a fly-in lake.  We didn't catch any brutes, but we lost track of how many of these we caught   My cousin with a few fish at camp.   Another little laker with a VERY bright coat   A natural brookie on a lake with predominantly namaycush   A nicer speck caught on the stocked lakes near town
nice  looks like fun  wish I had some back lake brookie lakes around here
Nice pictures those look like some nice Brook Trout. Sounds like a great day.
Hey Doc !!! I was half expectiong to hear about your bad day, but you cant get better than that !!! Nice trout Thanks for the report.
no way merc! the only bad thing about the day was the hike out!  nothing like hiking until your body shakes.
looks like a great outing --   love the first pic where you set one up eating the tale of the next
Wow !!!  And I wish I even had a 'stocked' lake near town !  (pm me which town )
So many brookies!  Nice catches Doc,
Very nice Doc !
Naw, i dont hike anymore. I get someone else to do it for me Mind you, i go like a lizard drinkin, on my recumbant bike
Great report Doc ! Gotta love those back lake trout excursions. I have a couple trips like that planned for May .
NIce report. Thanks for sharing.
Thanks for sharing Doc.  Whats with the potty? Let nature take it,s course.
SISU !!!
The potty goes everywhere.  Just to spend one afternoon at camp I had to make 3 trips on the sled with gear and toys the wife brought for my soon.
Great pics and fish! Some big brookies Doc
nice job!  Living up to your name.
Nice catch Doc. Everybody I talk to did great last weekend. I sure hope they are still hitting this weekend
Some great looking trout Luc! The last one is a fatty! Gearing up right now for tomorrow. Probably my last trip up to the park on the ice. The rest will be on the rivers!  TDunn
Nice Specks and lakers!  Teaser for the spring opener for sure..
Sweet looking Fish
As good as it gets.  Excellent.
A great day for sure.
Doesn't get any better than that. Great stuff!
Excellent Dr S!!! Wish trout season was open over here Ah well... April 22nd can't come soon enough Leechman
